subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 1b
). Tegumen narrow, gently arched, with a small notch at middle on posterior margin. Costal part of valva arched, wide basally, narrowed to pointed apex distally, sparsely setose, with a large sclerotized flap basally; saccular part of valva slightly shorter than costal part, gradually narrowed from base to basal 2/3; distal 1/3 digitate, with long sparse setae, rounded at apex. Juxta with basal 1/5 sub-quadrate, straight and sclerotized on anterior margin; distal 4/5 gradually narrowed to rounded apex, preapically with a cluster of spines, laterally between distal 2/5 and preapex with a large, sclerotized triangular flap curved inward. Aedeagus long and slender, about 1.5 times length of saccular part of valva, sclerotized, with short fine spines and gradules distally; cornuti consisting of a cluster of easily shed long spines bearing teeth basally.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 1c
). Papillae anales sub-cylindrical, rounded on posterior margin, with dense short setae posteriorly and with long setae anteriorly. Apophyses anteriores approximately half length of apophyses posteriores. Eighth tergite sub-rectangular; eighth sternite rounded and with long setae on posterior margin. Antrum membranous, sub-trapezoidal, concave on posterior margin on ventral surface. Ductus bursae membranous, enlarged anterad antrum; ductus seminalis arising from posterior 1/3 of ductus bursae. Corpus bursae ovoid, about 0.6 times length of ductus bursae; with two densely dentate signa, one signum ovoid, the other sub-rectangular.
